**     | `x.ai/session/*`     | `fork`, `resolve_local_for_worktree_resume`      |"}]},{"path":"/private/var/folders/rb/bzdrr2hj3x7db9mrc56chs440000gn/T/.tmpFSxEpj/.grok-home/docs/user-guide/21-terminal-support.md","matches":[{"line_number":165,"content":"forks) use xterm.js, which only partially implements the Kitty keyboard"}]},{"path":"/private/var/folders/rb/bzdrr2hj3x7db9mrc56chs440000gn/T/.tmpFSxEpj/.grok-home/docs/user-guide/14-headless-mode.md","matches":[{"line_number":26,"content":"| `--fork-session`        | With `-r`/`-c`, fork into a new session ID instead of appending to the original |"},{"line_number":179,"content":"To carry context across headless calls, use `-r/--resume` or `-c/--continue`. Use `-s/--session-id` only for a **new** session with a **UUID** (errors if not a UUID or already in use under the target directory). Older hidden `-s` upsert/resume behavior is gone — use `-r`/`-c` to continue. With `-r`/`-c`, `-s` requires `--fork-session`:"}]},{"path":"/private/var/folders/rb/bzdrr2hj3x7db9mrc56chs440000gn/T/.tmpFSxEpj/.grok-home/docs/user-guide/16-subagents.md","matches":[{"line_number":279,"content":"- Title bar inside the frame: status icon (spinner / ✓ / ✗), label + bold description + model, optional \"resumed\"/\"forked\" badge, live activity · elapsed time, and [✗] close button."}]},{"path":"/private/var/folders/rb/bzdrr2hj3x7db9mrc56chs440000gn/T/.tmpFSxEpj/.grok-home/docs/user-guide/17-sessions.md","matches":[{"line_number":39,"content":"`summary.json` is the index entry. It records the session summary and generated title, the model ID, the creation and update timestamps, the message counts, and a parent session reference for forked or restored sessions. `updates.jsonl` is the authoritative conversation log that drives `/resume` and session restore."},{"line_number":81,"content":"To switch between, rename, or close the sessions that are currently active (the parent session and any forks), use `/sessions` instead."},{"line_number":106,"content":"/fork [--worktree|--no-worktree] [directive]"},{"line_number":109,"content":"Pass an optional `directive` to set the new session's first prompt. Use `--worktree` or `--no-worktree` to choose whether the fork runs in a new git worktree; omit both to be asked each time. The `--at <turn>` flag is not supported in this version."},{"line_number":198,"content":"Use `-s`/`--session-id` only to **create** a new session with a **UUID** (errors if the value is not a UUID, or if that ID already has a session under the target session directory). It does **not** resume an existing session — that was the old hidden upsert behavior; use `-r`/`-c` instead. Combine `-s` with `-r`/`-c` only when also passing `--fork-session` (forks history into a new ID; optional `-s` names the child UUID). This matches Claude Code’s anti-overwrite model (client preflight under the write cwd; sequential use is reliable, concurrent same-ID is best-effort)."},{"line_number":252,"content":"When working with subagents or session forks, Grok can create isolated git worktrees per session. Each worktree gets its own copy of the working directory, so file changes in one session do not affect another."},{"line_number":285,"content":"- `parent_session_id` -- the source session for a fork or restore"}]},{"path":"/private/var/folders/rb/bzdrr2hj3x7db9mrc56chs440000gn/T/.tmpFSxEpj/.grok-home/docs/user-guide/05-configuration.md","matches":[{"line_number":379,"content":"fork_worktree_mode = \"ask\"             # /fork worktree prompt: \"ask\" | \"always\" | \"never\""},{"line_number":387,"content":"| `fork_worktree_mode` | string | `\"ask\"` | Worktree prompt for `/fork`: `ask`, `always`, or `never`. |"}]}]}},"_meta":{"totalTokens":23068,"eventId":"019f4fb2-9914-7191-a376-cce109321c40-224","agentTimestampMs":1783748626360,"promptId":"774514de-59df-46e8-8775-537ab3c280f4","streamStartMs":1783748623867,"turnStartMs":1783748622971,"updateType":"ToolCallUpdate","updateParams":{"toolCallId":"call-fecf24c5-330f